<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 12:01AM MDT  by NWS Riverton</headline>
<description>...Light Snow through 9 AM Sunday...
This is a special weather statement from the National Weather
Service Office in Riverton.
* WHAT...Light snow with new snowfall of an inch or two. Northwest
to north wind 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 45 mph. Low visibility
at times along with blowing and drifting snow.
* WHERE...Bighorn Mountains.
* WHEN...Now until 9 AM Sunday.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Roads are closed over Powder River Pass and
Granite Pass per the Wyoming Highway Department. These roads
will likely remain closed through Sunday morning.</description>
